{
  "text": "Cell immobilization was based on a two-phase dispersion process as previously described [CITATION_1] . A mixed gel of 2.5% (w/v) gelrite gellan gum and 0.25% (w/v) xanthan gum (both Sigma-Aldrich) was inoculated at 2% (v/v) with a pre-culture of B. longum NCC2705, containing ca. 10 9 CFU ml -1 . Beads with diameters in the range of 1.0-2.0 mm were selected by wet sieving and used for fermentation. The entire process was completed within 1 h.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8350690"
